comments: The song was written as almost the opposite to its meaning now. Jeremy Paul: We wanted a satirical Christmas carol when the little match girl is being kicked away into the snow by the unfeeling middle classes in a Dickensian setting. The turning point of it was when Twiggy sang it on a TV production of the show in 1987, retitled "The Little Matchgirl". By this time it had got itself into being used in a different way in the show - she sings it as a sort of pub song - she's playing the local whore. After a tip by his roadie, Cliff Richard heard the version from the TV production, liked the song but changed the lyrics to reflect a more religious theme (which the writers accepted).
